ğŸ”¹ Principles

Separation of Concerns

UI renders and collects input only

API enforces business rules, authentication, and validation

DATA layer is accessed exclusively via the API

Unidirectional Dependency

Flow is always UI â†’ API â†’ DATA

No layer bypasses the rules of the layer beneath it

Benefits

Maintainability â€“ Layers evolve independently

Testability â€“ Logic can be validated without UI coupling

Security â€“ Client cannot bypass server rules

Scalability â€“ UI and API scale independently

Longevity â€“ Architecture remains adaptable for future technologies

ğŸ”¹ Summary

By combining FFA pillars with a three-tier structure, this project ensures clarity, robustness, and future-proofing, making it suitable for modern web applications and complex software       
