a diagram concept:

+---------------------------------------------------------------+
|                        Shared JS CRUD Module                  |
|---------------------------------------------------------------|
| Functions:                                                    |
|  - attachRowEvents(row)     <---- Handles Update/Delete/Cancel
|  - saveRow(row)             <---- Handles insert or update
|  - enableEditing(row)       <---- Makes inputs editable
|  - disableEditing(row)      <---- Makes inputs read-only
|  - buildPayload(row, fields) <--- Converts row inputs to payload
|  - cursorManager.openRow(row) / closeRow(row) <--- Handles UI focus/scroll/highlight
+---------------------------------------------------------------+
               ^
               | (called from)
               |
+--------------------------------------------------------------+
|                        Table Rows (all pages)                |
|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Each row has:                                                |
|  - data-tab (p1-p10)                                         |
|  - data-id (primary key)                                     |
|  - data-state (new/saved/editing)                            |
|  - Buttons: update / save / cancel / delete                  |
|  - Inputs with field classes                                 |
|  - Event listeners attached via attachRowEvents(row)         |
+--------------------------------------------------------------+
               ^
               | (new rows only)
               |
+--------------------------------------------------------------+
|                       Add Button (pages 4,5,6)               |
|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| - Calls addRow(tab)                                          |
| - Creates a new row at bottom of table                       |
| - Attaches same attachRowEvents(row) for shared behavior     |
+--------------------------------------------------------------+
